Be vigilant. That s the most important thing to remember. History has shown us that during the festive period people tend to be complacent and at times oblivious about their surroundings resulting in them becoming victims of crime said spokesman Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo.Here are the holiday safety tips: Money is the primary motivation for many crimes. Avoid carrying large sums of cash. Use bank cards instead. Members of stokvels should speak to banks about alternatives to having to withdraw deposits.